node.title: Queensland on track to hit 80pc vaccination as no new COVID-19 community cases detected
node.alt: Annastacia Palaszczuk speaks at a press conference in Brisbane.
node.description: Queensland records no new community cases of COVID-19 overnight and detects three new cases in hotel quarantine – two travellers from overseas and one from interstate.
node.content:
["Queensland has recorded no new community cases of COVID-19.", "The state has detected three new cases in hotel quarantine \u2013 two travellers\u00a0from overseas and one from interstate.", "There is currently a small cluster in the Queensland border town of Goondiwindi, with 5,826 tests done in the past 24 hours.\u00a0", "Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk said the state looked\u00a0set to hit 80 per cent\u00a0of the eligible population over 16 years with a first dose of a COVID-19 vaccine by Tuesday.", "About 14,000 vaccines were administered by Queensland Health on Saturday.", "Speaking from a hardware store in the Brisbane suburb of Stafford, Ms Palaszczuk said more than 2,000 vaccines were administered through hardware stores on Saturday.", "\"More than 50 per cent were first doses, and what we're seeing on the north side of Brisbane, is that they're young people, so that's fantastic,\" she said.", "\"That's the cohort we're concerned about at the moment.\"", "Ms Palaszczuk said the state's first dose rate was now at 73 per cent.", "Almost 67 per cent of eligible Queenslanders over 16 years old are now fully vaccinated.\u00a0", "Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken said contact tracing details for the three new cases in quarantine were being worked through.", "\"One of those is someone who's travelled interstate from Melbourne,\" he said.", "\"They were potentially infectious on the flight. That's being worked through at the moment and the flight number will be available on the website shortly, as well as any contact tracing details once we get information from the airline.\"", "", "
Queensland\u00a0Acting Chief Health Officer Dr Peter Aitken\u00a0speaks at a press conference in Brisbane on November 7, 2021.\u00a0(ABC News: Tobias Jurss-Lewis)
", "Dr Aitken said the two international travellers who tested positive had travelled from the Ukraine via Dubai.", "Authorities have now confirmed a fourth case connected to the Goondiwindi cluster announced yesterday, was not infectious in the community.", "Dr Aitken said they were also continuing to work through the details of a woman linked to Cairns who travelled to Darwin \u2013 currently in a lockout\u00a0after a positive case emerged in the Top End.", "\"The information we received from the Northern Territory last night was that she hadn't been infectious in the community, based on her testing and onset of symptoms,\" he said.", "\"That information continues to evolve and there's been further interviews today \u2026 it's a really great reminder, and I would ask everyone in the Cairns, Cardwell, Innisfail region, if you've had any symptoms at all to come forward and get tested so we can be completely certain.\"", "
'Cautiously optimistic'
", "Ms Palaszczuk said the state was \"absolutely\" on track to hit its predicted date for 80 per cent fully vaccinated.", "Dr Aitken said they were feeling \"cautiously optimistic\" about the Goondiwindi cluster.", "\"It's early days still, we haven't got through a full incubation period,\" he said.", "\"At this stage, the fact there's been no new cases \u2014 no community transmission \u2014 the only cases have been identified close contacts is really positive news.", "\"I think its testament again to the Goondiwindi community with their high vaccination rates.", "\"Optimistic, hopeful, not quite there.\"", "", "
